{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Conditional on these (unobserved) community labels, edges are generated independently, with probabilities depending only on the communities of the connected nodes.",
    "In its simplest form, the within-community connection probability is p, while the between-community connection probability is q, with p > q.",
    "This model captures community structure in a mathematically tractable way and has been widely studied in statistics, computer science, and probability theory [Abb18].",
    "The central inferential task in SBM analysis is to recover the latent community memberships from an observed network.",
    "In the sparse regime, where q scales as 1/n, the seminal paper of Decelle, Krzakala, Moore, and Zdeborová [Dec+11] conjectured -based on the replica heuristic from statistical physics-that, when K is fixed and n → +∞, community recovery in polynomial-time is possible only above the Kesten-Stigum (KS) threshold nλ 2 Kλ + K 2 q > 1."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This model captures community structure in a mathematically tractable way and has been widely studied in statistics, computer science, and probability theory [Abb18].",
    "In the sparse regime, where q scales as 1/n, the seminal paper of Decelle, Krzakala, Moore, and Zdeborová [Dec+11] conjectured -based on the replica heuristic from statistical physics-that, when K is fixed and n → +∞, community recovery in polynomial-time is possible only above the Kesten-Stigum (KS) threshold nλ 2 Kλ + K 2 q > 1."
